items.title: Chartist Talks: I-Sec’s Dharmesh Shah sees strong Nifty structure despite recent correction; expects index to reach 25,800 in August
items.description: I-Sec’s Dharmesh Shah expects volatility to remain elevated amid progression of earnings season coupled with Tariff related development wherein strong support is placed at 24,900-24,800 levels.

items.title: TCS shares tumble 3.5% after Q1 earnings fail to impress markets; drag down all IT stocks
items.description: TCS reported a 6% rise in Q1 net profit to Rs 12,760 crore, beating expectations. The company’s revenue from operations meanwhile rose 1.3% to Rs 63,437 crore during the quarter under review.
